atic.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Gradle support**\\n\\nI need to think about building support. Maybe I ought to patch the build.gradle file to use the module path? I wonder if Gradle supports that, especially if the module-info file is present? It feels like there’s a lot of uncertainty, but making sure I get this right for the build process is really important. I'll keep exploring this avenue to find the best solution!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JHOUoe6NEsVqvnRKKwZpQAO0|fc_0a6beee47f3b5c1b016a2c0ef195548197b76d98ac1a7f93e0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build -name 'mockito-core-5.0.0.jar' -o -name '*.jar' | head -20 && rg \"Automatic-Module-Name|module\" /home/mihailo/git/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/main/extracted -n | head -50", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 194, "output": 2209, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32099, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781272253139, "responseId": "resp_0a6beee47f3b5c1b016a2c0ebde6ac8197bd6540d0a2a294c2"}}
